frameDefinitions: A Perceiver determines the Location of a Sought_entity within a Ground.
A Landmark (in combination with the image schema evoked by particular targets) serves to pick out the final location of a Trajector in a construed or actual motion event.
A Current_country is identified as matching or not matching the instance of the Discourse_salient_country.
A Helper benefits a Benefited_party by enabling the culmination of a Goal that the Benefited_party has.
A Person usually resides or works in a Location.
This frame covers the basic uses of direction words like the adverbs east, up, and forward.
frameExamples: Kim <t>found</t> his hat on the far side.
Flights <t>into</t> Denver are not permitted at this time.
<t><fex name='cur'>Foreign</fex></t> sales account for only 20% of IBM's income .
Will you <t>help</t> the Government find your brother?
listRoleDefinitions: The individual that determines the <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Perceiver</fen> succeeds in finding.
The position of the <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The general set of entities that the <fen>Perceiver</fen> examined in order to find the <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Sought_entity</fen> is located.
The relatively locatable entity which serves as a basis for determining the location of the <fen>Trajector</fen> using the <fen>Profiled_region</fen>.
The entity which is construed to be in motion, whose location at the end of the construed motion event is in question.
The time at which the <fen>Trajector</fen> is located in the <fen>Profiled_region</fen>.
The country or countries that the speaker is indicating in the current instance, which may match or be distinct from the <fen>Discourse_salient_country</fen>.

The country that has been featured in the discourse, or that the speaker/hearer identify with or are located in; it serves to identify the <fen>Current_country</fen> by specifying it as the same or different.  This role is incorporated in the targets of this frame.
The <fen>Benefited_party</fen> receives a benefit from the action of the <fen>Helper</fen>.
The <fen>Helper</fen> performs some action that benefits the <fen>Benefited_party</fen>.
The desirable state of affairs that the <fen>Benefited_party</fen> is involved in and which is enabled by the <fen>Helper</fen>.
This role identifies a <fen>Focal_entity</fen> involved in achieving the <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Assistance occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the Assistance occurs.
The <fen>Location</fen>  is the place of business or residence prototypically occupied by the <fen>Person</fen>.
The <fen>Person</fen> is located in or at a place that they customarily occupy.
The time period during which the <fen>Person</fen> occupies the <fen>Location</fen>.
The one-dimensional set of locations.
listRoleExamples: <fex>I</fex> finally found the peanut underneath the couch cusion.
Sam located the Imperial regal <fex>among the coins in his pocket</fex> and passed it to the boy.
AutoPartsPlace.com offers discount prices on millions of import auto parts, <fex><t>domestic</t></fex> car parts, and car accessories.
Whoever didn't cook has to help <fex>with the dishes</fex>.
The police assisted Harry in finding his cat <fex>on Wednesday afternoon</fex>.
The police assisted Harry in finding his cat <fex>in front of his house</fex>.

I couldn't access the details of prospective buyers and sellers and was
uncontactable when I was out <fex>of the office</fex>.
<fex>The doctor</fex> is not in right now.
Call work, tell them you'll be in <fex>in the afternoon</fex>.
